  "prompt": "What are some ways to restore a Compaq computer to factory settings?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to restore a Compaq computer to factory settings:\n\n1. Recovery Partition Method\n- Restart the computer\n- Press F11 during startup\n- Select \"System Recovery\" or similar option\n- Follow on-screen instructions to restore factory settings\n\n2. Recovery Disk Method\n- Insert the recovery disk that came with the computer\n- Restart and boot from the disk\n- Follow restore/reset instructions\n\n3. Windows Recovery Options\n- Open Settings\n- Select \"Update & Security\"\n- Choose \"Recovery\"\n- Select \"Reset this PC\"\n- Choose to keep or remove personal files\n\n4. BIOS Recovery Option\n- Restart computer\n- Press appropriate key (F10, F2, etc.) to enter BIOS\n- Look for reset or recovery options\n\n5. Manufacturer's Recovery Software\n- Some Compaq models have specific recovery software\n- Access through Start menu or recovery partition\n\n6. Command Prompt Reset\n- Boot into advanced startup options\n- Use command prompt reset tools\n\nImportant considerations:\n- Back up important files before resetting\n- Ensure you have necessary recovery media\n- Follow specific instructions for your exact Compaq model\n\nIf unsure, consult Compaq/HP support documentation or contact their customer support.",
